On 26/04/07, Gordon Mohr &lt;gojomo@...&gt; wrote:
&gt;  Heritrix and the DNSJava library are all-Java -- so can&#39;t be directly
&gt;  responsible for a memory-access crash like this.
&gt;
&gt;  The crash log you sent indicated the crash occurred in the runtime&#39;s
&gt;  background finalization thread, with regard to a DatagramChannelImpl and
&gt;  FileDispatcher.preClose.
&gt;
&gt;  This JVM bug against Java 1.7 (&quot;dolphin&quot;) at Sun seems related:
&gt;
&gt;  http://bugs.sun.com/bugdatabase/view_bug.do?bug_id=6497734
&gt;
&gt;  I&#39;ve reported to Sun that the bug exists in 1.6 (and based on other
&gt;  reports here and in that Sun bug, in 1.5 as well) so that they might
&gt;  backport the fix.
&gt;
&gt;  Their closed 1.7 bug also suggests the real problem is a depletion of
&gt;  file handles, which leaves the channel uninitialized. So you might be
&gt;  able to avoid the problem by making more handles available. This FAQ,
&gt;  while for a different error, thus may help:
&gt;
&gt;  http://crawler.archive.org/faq.html#toomanyopenfiles

